# Project Management JWT API

Mini Project Management REST API built with Spring Boot, PostgreSQL and JWT Authentication.

## Quick start

1. Ensure PostgreSQL is running and a database named `manager` exists:
```sql
CREATE DATABASE manager;
```

2. Update `src/main/resources/application.properties` if needed:
```
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/manager
spring.datasource.username=harsh
spring.datasource.password=root
jwt.secret=mysecretkey12345
jwt.expiration-ms=1200000
```

3. Build and run:
```bash
mvn clean package
mvn spring-boot:run
```

4. Postman flow:
- Register:
  POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
  Body: { "username": "harsh", "password": "1234" }
- Login:
  POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
  Body: { "username": "harsh", "password": "1234" }
  Response: { "token": "..." }
- Use token in Authorization header:
  Authorization: Bearer <token>

5. Example create project:
  POST /api/projects
  Header: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  Body: { "name":"My Project", "description":"desc" }

6. Example create task:
  POST /api/projects/{projectId}/tasks
  Header: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  Body: { "title":"Task 1", "description":"desc", "priority":"HIGH", "status":"PENDING", "dueDate":"2025-12-01" }

## Notes
- Java 17
- Lombok recommended for IDE
- Token expiry: 20 minutes (1200000 ms)
